    <div class="first">
        <section>
            <h2>About the Legend</h2>
            <p>
                1. Name : Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam.<br><br>
2. Birth : Born on October 15, 1931, in Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu, India.<br><br>
3. Education : Graduated in Physics from St. Joseph's College, Tiruchirappalli, and later studied aerospace engineering at the Madras Institute of Technology (MIT).<br><br>
4. Career : Started his career at the Defense Research and Development Organization (DRDO) and later joined the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO).<br><br>
5. Role in ISRO : Played a key role in India's space program, particularly in developing ballistic missile technology.<br><br>
6. Missile Man of India : Known for his work on the development of the Agni and Prithvi missiles.<br><br>
7. Pokhran-II Tests : Led the scientific team in the successful Pokhran-II nuclear tests in 1998.<br><br>
8. 11th President of India : Served as the President of India from 2002 to 2007, becoming known as the "People's President."<br><br>
9. Vision 2020 : Advocated for India's development through his Vision 2020 plan, which aimed at transforming India into a developed nation.<br><br>
10. Books : Authored several books, including "Wings of Fire" (his autobiography), "Ignited Minds," and "India 2020."<br><br>
11. Awards : Received numerous awards, including the Bharat Ratna, India's highest civilian honor.<br>
12. Inspirational Figure : Inspired millions, especially the youth, through his speeches and writings on education, science, and nation-building.<br><br>
13. Simple Lifestyle : Known for his humility, simple living, and dedication to public service.<br><br>
14. Death : Passed away on July 27, 2015, while delivering a lecture at the Indian Institute of Management, Shillong.<br><br>
15. Legacy : Remembered as one of India's most beloved leaders and a symbol of national pride.<br><br>
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
